features: SENSORY PLAY: With 17 sensory activities, the Busy Buggy will provide endless entertainment for your toddler! These activities encourage imaginative play and include interlocking gears, sliding beads, a clicking spare tire, and more

DEVELOP MOTOR SKILLS: This ride-on for 1 year old’s has three modes of play: push walker, ride-on, and sensory play. These modes help toddlers gain confidence in walking and develop fine and gross motor skills

WALK & RIDE: This is both a baby push walker and ride-on, allowing children to build confidence and balance as they learn to walk. Equipped with an anti-tip feature on the back of the car, the Busy Buggy is safe for beginner walkers

body.description: Radio Flyer’s Busy Buggy is a new, interactive ride-on that encourages imagitive play and helps develop both fine and gross motor skills. It is also a push walker, which allows children to build confidence and balance as they learn to walk. With 17 interactive sensory activities, the Busy Buggy will provide endless learning and fun! Interactive activities include interlocking gears, a clicking spare tire, folding side view mirrors, a spinning steering wheel and more. The spinning beads introduce letters and numbers. Storage underneath the seat allows your child’s favorite toys to join every adventure. For ages 1 3 years. For additional questions, support, or concerns, please contact our customer service team at https://www.radioflyer.com/customer-service/ or 1 (800) 621-7613.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My grandson loved this item!!
reviews.reviewText: The Radio Flyer Busy Buggy Ride On Toy is a delightful and engaging companion for young children aged 1-3. As a parent seeking a ride-on toy that promotes both fun and developmental growth, I am thoroughly impressed with the Busy Buggy. Here's my review of this vibrant and versatile ride-on toy from Radio Flyer.First and foremost, the design of the Busy Buggy is captivating. Its bright red color, coupled with the friendly face on the front, instantly appeals to children. The attention to detail is remarkable, as the buggy features interactive elements such as a clicking gearshift, a clicking steering wheel, and a movable honking horn. These features provide a multisensory experience, stimulating the child's imagination and encouraging interactive play. The durability of the Busy Buggy is noteworthy. It is built to withstand the rough and tumble play of active toddlers. The sturdy construction and high-quality materials ensure that this ride-on toy can endure years of use. The easy-to-clean surface is another practical aspect that parents will appreciate, as it allows for quick and hassle-free maintenance. In summary, the Radio Flyer Busy Buggy Ride On Toy is a fantastic choice for young children. Its engaging design, interactive features, and versatility make it an excellent tool for promoting both play and developmental growth. The safety features and durability further contribute to its appeal. Whether children are sitting or standing, the Busy Buggy provides endless fun and learning opportunities. For parents seeking a ride-on toy that combines entertainment, development, and safety, the Busy Buggy is an exceptional choice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My 18 month old is obsessed.
reviews.reviewText: My 18 month old loves this. It is the perfect first ride on toy. The wheels aren’t going to turn or anything like that with a steering wheel. But, it’s easy to assemble. Easy for them to get on and off. He loves all the little extra toys on it and that the seat can hide stuff! I don’t think you can beat it for the price. When shopping for a ride on toy, I came across a lot of them that were way more expensive than this. I’m so happy that I went with something like this. It doesn’t have any automated noises or need batteries but it still has fun toys and my som is super interested in them. A Total win in my book. My kiddo played with it almost all day long.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Wish the steering wheel worked
reviews.reviewText: This car is great first big toy car for our 18 month old, I only have 2 complaints and that's why I give it four stars.#1 The steering wheel doesn't actually turn the front two wheels in any direction. This car only goes in a straight line, which makes it hard for our child to actually ride this and turn corners.#2 The little seat cover opens, but it opens towards the steering wheel and therefore doesn't stay open, which frustrates the toddler when he wants it to stay open so he can put toys inside it.Otherwise very cute, not too big or bulky. No assembly required.Shipped properly.
